<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>On Thursday, a 45-year-old cop was killed outside his house in Jama Street, Khayelitsha at 8.35pm while off duty.Lieutenant-Colonel Andre Traut said: “The two unknown suspects demanded his firearm, which he had left at the police station for safekeeping. They fled the scene with a cellular phone and an undisclosed amount of cash. “They are yet to be arrested.” The family of the dead policeman from Lentegeur Police Station refused to speak to the SunTeam. They said they were shocked by the incident and weren’t ready to talk about it.Witnesses said the cop was shot at close range. The thugs apparently searched the house after the shooting and fled with his phone and cash.Lieutenant-General Khombinkosi Jula said: “We will apply our resources wisely to catch the two suspects who killed one of our members last night in Khayelitsha.” He said they remain focused on Marikana and other areas in the province affected by crime. The police appealed to anyone with information that could help with the arrest of the two suspects to come forward and call CrimeStop on 08600 10111.Meanwhile, 120 Marikana suspects were bust on Friday on charges ranging from armed robbery to rape, possession of unlicenced firearms and drug dealing.